definitions.definition: In Anglo-Saxon society, land held by charter or written title , free from all fief , fee, service , and fines. It was held chiefly by the nobility and denominated freeholders .

main_definition: ( historical ) In Anglo-Saxon society, land held by charter or written title , free from all fief , fee, service , and fines. It was held chiefly by the nobility and denominated freeholders .
